  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (9ed1c37 2022-08-01T00:09:10.803586Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nFoundry does not detect when contracts exceed the contract size limit when deploying to a live network. The transaction is sent nonetheless, but fails.\r\nOne might argue that this should be set by the user, however I do imagine this being problematic when deploying to mainnet.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1084\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/103113487/182136968-eb6d8752-d523-4b1f-9518-68b4bdd12803.png\">\r\n",
